Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with embedding a planar graph as a convex 3-polytope, which is a topic in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The algorithmic aspect of the paper involves finding a convex plane embedding with certain properties, which is a problem in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of discrete objects (graphs and polytopes) and their properties, which falls under the purview of discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves the study of geometric objects (polytopes) and their properties, which is a topic in game theory. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with the visualization of geometric objects (polytopes) and their embeddings, which is a topic in computer graphics.
